Budapest Bank Rt has become the firstof the commercial banks operating since January to issue bondsto expand its resources, the official Hungarian news agency MTIsaid.    The seven-year bonds totalling 500 mln forints may be takenup by companies, cooperatives and enterprises, MTI said.    The interest rate will always be 0.5 points above thatcharged to commercial banks by the National Bank of Hungary forloans exceeding one year. This year's rate will thus be 11 pct.    The funds raised will be used to increase the bank'sinvestment loan offer for small and medium-sized companies. REUTER&#3;